==English==

===Etymology===
From french [[assister]], from latin [[assistere]] both meaning to assist.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}} 
# ''(sports)'' [[statistic]]al recognition of making a [[pass]] that leads directly towards [[scoring]].
#:''He had two '''assists''' in the game.''

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Finnish: [[syöttö]]
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|assist||}}
# To [[help]] someone.
#: ''Would you please '''assist''' John with learning English.''
# ''(sports)'' To make a pass that leads directly towards scoring.

